# PDR-019 U6 / lead-8vxy (owner: shopsystem-templates; request_bugfix — reshapes
# the existing ops provision body). Make bin/agent-vault-provision lead-driveable
# so the lead can provision FOR the user (INSTALL §2/§3): the non-secret +
# non-OAuth-secret inputs (owner password, GitHub username/PAT) arrive via env/args
# — NO interactive "read -s" for those — and the ONE genuine human step (approving
# the CLAUDE_OAUTH proposal) is isolated into a clean, lead-presentable handoff:
# the lead runs provision, captures the proposal number and the exact
# "proposal approve <num> CLAUDE_OAUTH=<value> --yes" command, hands it to the user,
# and resumes.
#
# RESHAPES features/agent-vault-broker/10 @scenario_hash:4ecd3b661ddf4713 — the
# "exactly one human-gated paste" model becomes "env-driven inputs + a single
# approval handoff".
# PRESERVES features/agent-vault-broker/11 @scenario_hash:72af524bca85f59c — the
# real OAuth secret is supplied only at approve-time (ADR-026 D4) and no automated
# step transports a real credential; this scenario must not weaken that guarantee.
@scenario_hash:1d08c456af08d577 @bc:shopsystem-templates
  Scenario: provision takes non-OAuth inputs via env/args and isolates the OAuth approval into a lead-presentable handoff
    Given a running agent-vault broker with an empty vault
    And the owner password and the GitHub username and PAT are supplied via environment variables or arguments
    When the lead runs bin/agent-vault-provision
    Then it consumes the owner password and the GitHub username and PAT from the environment or arguments without any interactive prompt
    And it stores the GitHub credential in the vault without the lead handling any real Claude OAuth secret
    And it creates a CLAUDE_OAUTH proposal and reports the proposal number together with the exact "proposal approve <num> CLAUDE_OAUTH=<value> --yes" command for the user to run
    And the real Claude OAuth secret is supplied only at approve-time and no automated step transports it
